<ul data-start="419" data-end="715">
<li data-start="419" data-end="481">
<p data-start="421" data-end="481">Landauer’s principle and the thermodynamic cost of erasure</p>
</li>
<li data-start="482" data-end="555">
<p data-start="484" data-end="555">Bennett’s reversible computation as a <em data-start="522" data-end="528">foil</em> rather than a foundation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="556" data-end="637">
<p data-start="558" data-end="637">Why Spherepop formalizes irreversibility as syntax, not implementation detail</p>
</li>
<li data-start="638" data-end="715">
<p data-start="640" data-end="715">Distinction between physical irreversibility and <em data-start="689" data-end="715">semantic irreversibility</em></p>
