Below is a <strong data-start="95" data-end="116">new LaTeX section</strong> you can insert <strong data-start="132" data-end="178">immediately after the Psychocinema section</strong>, or as a subsection within it. It explains why Spherepop <em data-start="236" data-end="247">naturally</em> affords a <strong data-start="258" data-end="309">2D/3D visual language of nested bubbles/spheres</strong>, and why this is not merely illustrative but structurally faithful.</p>
