<h3 data-start="3483" data-end="3514">Why this bibliography works</h3>
<ul data-start="3516" data-end="3886">
<li data-start="3516" data-end="3539">
<p data-start="3518" data-end="3539"><strong data-start="3518" data-end="3539">No self-citations</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="3540" data-end="3886">
<p data-start="3542" data-end="3549">Covers:</p>
<ul data-start="3552" data-end="3886">
<li data-start="3552" data-end="3590">
<p data-start="3554" data-end="3590">irreversibility (Landauer, Bennett),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3593" data-end="3646">
<p data-start="3595" data-end="3646">category theory &amp; sheaves (Mac Lane, Grothendieck),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3649" data-end="3699">
<p data-start="3651" data-end="3699">action/constraint thinking (Jacobson, Verlinde),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3702" data-end="3746">
<p data-start="3704" data-end="3746">cognition &amp; agency (Friston, Marr, Ashby),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3749" data-end="3798">
<p data-start="3751" data-end="3798">philosophy of worldhood (Heidegger, Whitehead),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3801" data-end="3840">
<p data-start="3803" data-end="3840">contrast frameworks (Lacan, Deleuze),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3843" data-end="3886">
<p data-start="3845" data-end="3886">computation foundations (Turing, Girard).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3888" data-end="3966">It reads as <strong data-start="3900" data-end="3946">serious, interdisciplinary, and defensible</strong>, not manifesto-ish.</p>
<p data-start="3968" data-end="3992">If you want next, I can:</p>
<ul data-start="3993" data-end="4181" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="3993" data-end="4051">
<p data-start="3995" data-end="4051">tailor this bibliography to a <strong data-start="4025" data-end="4045">specific journal</strong>, or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4052" data-end="4109">
<p data-start="4054" data-end="4109">prune it to a <strong data-start="4068" data-end="4103">leaner, more formal math/CS cut</strong>, or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4110" data-end="4181" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="4112" data-end="4181" data-is-last-node="">add <strong data-start="4116" data-end="4151">brief in-text citation guidance</strong> (where each cluster belongs).</p>
