<hr data-start="4226" data-end="4229">
<h3 data-start="4231" data-end="4276">Why these additions matter (conceptually)</h3>
<ul data-start="4278" data-end="4617">
<li data-start="4278" data-end="4361">
<p data-start="4280" data-end="4361"><strong data-start="4280" data-end="4306">Heidegger (Technology)</strong> grounds your critique of state-machines and enframing.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4362" data-end="4445">
<p data-start="4364" data-end="4445"><strong data-start="4364" data-end="4375">Needham</strong> legitimizes your visual / geometric reasoning style without diagrams.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4446" data-end="4523">
<p data-start="4448" data-end="4523"><strong data-start="4448" data-end="4463">Erik Meijer</strong> anchors the endofunctor / parser view in serious PL theory.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4524" data-end="4617">
<p data-start="4526" data-end="4617"><strong data-start="4526" data-end="4553">Rollins’ <em data-start="4537" data-end="4551">Psychocinema</em></strong> formally supports the Lacanian contrast you explicitly develop.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="4619" data-end="4650">This bibliography now reads as:</p>
<blockquote data-start="4651" data-end="4750">
<p data-start="4653" data-end="4750"><em data-start="4653" data-end="4748">philosophically grounded, mathematically literate, computation-aware, and culturally informed</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="4752" data-end="4797">— exactly the profile your paper already has.</p>
<p data-start="4799" data-end="4823">If you want, next I can:</p>
<ul data-start="4824" data-end="4943" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="4824" data-end="4881">
<p data-start="4826" data-end="4881">prune this to a <strong data-start="4842" data-end="4875">strict philosophy journal cut</strong>, or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4882" data-end="4943" data-is-last-node="">
