<p data-start="167" data-end="329">Below I’ll show you <strong data-start="187" data-end="221">exactly how to do this cleanly</strong>, in a way reviewers expect, using <strong data-start="256" data-end="285">BibTeX + inline citations</strong>, while preserving your prose and structure.</p>
<hr data-start="331" data-end="334">
<h2 data-start="336" data-end="384">1. Choose a citation style (minimal friction)</h2>
<p data-start="386" data-end="448">For interdisciplinary papers like this, the safest default is:</p>
<ul data-start="450" data-end="530">
<li data-start="450" data-end="486">
<p data-start="452" data-end="486"><strong data-start="452" data-end="467">Author–year</strong> citations inline</p>
</li>
<li data-start="487" data-end="507">
<p data-start="489" data-end="507"><code data-start="489" data-end="497">natbib</code> package</p>
</li>
<li data-start="508" data-end="530">
<p data-start="510" data-end="530">Plain BibTeX backend</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="532" data-end="602">This works for philosophy, CS, cognitive science, and theory journals.</p>
<h3 data-start="604" data-end="633">Add this to your preamble</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="635" data-end="696"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\usepackage</span></span><span>{natbib}
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\bibliographystyle</span></span><span>{plainnat}
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="698" data-end="716">Now you can write:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="718" data-end="792"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{heidegger</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>being</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>time}
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citet</span></span><span>{landauer</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>irreversibility}
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<ul data-start="794" data-end="854">
<li data-start="794" data-end="825">
<p data-start="796" data-end="825"><code data-start="796" data-end="806">\citep{}</code> → (Author, Year)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="826" data-end="854">
<p data-start="828" data-end="854"><code data-start="828" data-end="838">\citet{}</code> → Author (Year)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="856" data-end="859">
<h2 data-start="861" data-end="908">2. Move your bibliography into a <code data-start="897" data-end="903">.bib</code> file</h2>
<p data-start="910" data-end="944">Create a file called, for example:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="946" data-end="971"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">text</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-text"><span><span>spherepop.bib
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="973" data-end="1046">Then convert your existing <code data-start="1000" data-end="1017">thebibliography</code> entries into BibTeX entries.</p>
<h3 data-start="1048" data-end="1071">Example conversions</h3>
<h4 data-start="1073" data-end="1106">Heidegger — <em data-start="1090" data-end="1106">Being and Time</em></h4>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1108" data-end="1351"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">bibtex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-bibtex"><span>@book{heidegger_being_time,
  author    = {Heidegger, Martin},
  title     = {Being and Time},
  translator= {Macquarrie, John and Robinson, Edward},
  year      = {1962},
  publisher = {Harper \&amp; Row},
  address   = {New York}
}
</span></code></div></div></pre>
<h4 data-start="1353" data-end="1384">Landauer — irreversibility</h4>
