<hr data-start="1992" data-end="1995">
<h2 data-start="1997" data-end="2063">3. Replace implicit reliance with inline citations (surgically)</h2>
<p data-start="2065" data-end="2126">You <strong data-start="2069" data-end="2079">do not</strong> need to add citations everywhere. The goal is:</p>
<ul data-start="2128" data-end="2221">
<li data-start="2128" data-end="2159">
<p data-start="2130" data-end="2159">Cite <strong data-start="2135" data-end="2159">at conceptual pivots</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2160" data-end="2180">
<p data-start="2162" data-end="2180">Not every sentence</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2181" data-end="2221">
<p data-start="2183" data-end="2221">Not after formulas unless interpretive</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2223" data-end="2332">Below are <strong data-start="2233" data-end="2278">examples mapped directly to your sections</strong>, showing <em data-start="2288" data-end="2297">exactly</em> where citations naturally slot in.</p>
<hr data-start="2334" data-end="2337">
<h2 data-start="2339" data-end="2373">4. Concrete examples by section</h2>
<h3 data-start="2375" data-end="2415">Section 1 — Axiom of Irreversibility</h3>
<p data-start="2417" data-end="2442">Original prose (example):</p>
<blockquote data-start="2444" data-end="2501">
<p data-start="2446" data-end="2501">In Spherepop, the world is a history to be constructed.</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="2503" data-end="2512">Refactor:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2514" data-end="2733"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>In Spherepop, the world is not a state to be updated but a history to be constructed, a move that aligns temporality with facticity rather than representation </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{heidegger</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>being</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>time,whitehead</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>process}.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="2735" data-end="2738">
<h3 data-start="2740" data-end="2779">Section 3 — Mechanics of Commitment</h3>
<p data-start="2781" data-end="2790">Original:</p>
<blockquote data-start="2792" data-end="2846">
<p data-start="2794" data-end="2846">We define the configuration variable as optionality.</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="2848" data-end="2857">Refactor:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2859" data-end="3164"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>We define the configuration variable as optionality, treating freedom as a consumable resource rather than a conserved quantity, in the spirit of thermodynamic interpretations of structure and information </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{landauer</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>irreversibility,bennett</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>logical</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>reversibility,jacobson</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>thermodynamics}.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3166" data-end="3169">
<h3 data-start="3171" data-end="3195">Psychocinema section</h3>
<p data-start="3197" data-end="3226">Original conceptual contrast:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="3228" data-end="3345"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>This retroactive construction of meaning contrasts sharply with the forward-only semantics of Spherepop.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="3347" data-end="3356">Refactor:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="3358" data-end="3638"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>This retroactive construction of meaning, characteristic of Lacanian and cinematic interpretations of subjectivity </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{lacan</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>four</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>fundamental,deleuze</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>cinema2,rollins</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>psychocinema</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>2024}, contrasts sharply with the forward-only, non-revisable semantics of Spherepop.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3640" data-end="3643">
<h3 data-start="3645" data-end="3680">Visualization section (Needham)</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="3682" data-end="3981"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>Because the calculus is formulated in terms of nested option--spaces, its visual realization preserves semantics rather than merely illustrating them, following the tradition of geometric reasoning as a primary explanatory tool </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{needham</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>visual</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>complex,needham</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>geometry</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>imaginary}.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3983" data-end="3986">
<h3 data-start="3988" data-end="4029">Endofunctor / parser section (Meijer)</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="4031" data-end="4287"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>Interpreting the agent as an endofunctor emphasizes world-transformation over state-transition, a perspective that aligns naturally with categorical approaches to computation </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{lawvere</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>adjoints,maclane</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>categories,meijer</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>category</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>effects}.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="4289" data-end="4292">
<h3 data-start="4294" data-end="4311">Sheaf section</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="4313" data-end="4509"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>Collapse may be understood as a form of sheafification, enforcing global coherence by identifying distinctions that obstruct gluing </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\citep</span></span><span>{grothendieck</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>sga1,maclane</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>moerdijk</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>sheaves}.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="4511" data-end="4514">
<h2 data-start="4516" data-end="4566">5. Add bibliography at the end (BibTeX version)</h2>
<p data-start="4568" data-end="4610">Replace your <code data-start="4581" data-end="4598">thebibliography</code> block with:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="4612" data-end="4649"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\bibliography</span></span><span>{spherepop}
