<hr data-start="1049" data-end="1052">
<h2 data-start="1054" data-end="1111">2. Why traditional diff/merge is the wrong abstraction</h2>
<p data-start="1113" data-end="1175">Standard tools like <code data-start="1133" data-end="1139">diff</code>, <code data-start="1141" data-end="1147">meld</code>, or <code data-start="1152" data-end="1163">git merge</code> operate on:</p>
<ul data-start="1177" data-end="1217">
<li data-start="1177" data-end="1185">
<p data-start="1179" data-end="1185">lines,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1186" data-end="1195">
<p data-start="1188" data-end="1195">tokens,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1196" data-end="1217">
<p data-start="1198" data-end="1217">or character spans.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1219" data-end="1231">They assume:</p>
<blockquote data-start="1232" data-end="1261">
<p data-start="1234" data-end="1261">identity = textual equality</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="1263" data-end="1299">But your actual decision process is:</p>
<blockquote data-start="1300" data-end="1349">
<p data-start="1302" data-end="1349">identity = semantic intention + structural role</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="1351" data-end="1397">That mismatch is why the process feels clumsy.</p>
<p data-start="1399" data-end="1475">You are already doing something <em data-start="1431" data-end="1455">strictly more powerful</em> than textual merge:</p>
<ul data-start="1477" data-end="1688">
<li data-start="1477" data-end="1541">
<p data-start="1479" data-end="1541">You compare <strong data-start="1491" data-end="1512">sections as roles</strong> (axiom, contrast, synthesis)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1542" data-end="1613">
<p data-start="1544" data-end="1613">You compare <strong data-start="1556" data-end="1578">sentences as moves</strong> (definition, justification, pivot)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1614" data-end="1688">
<p data-start="1616" data-end="1688">You accept rewrites that preserve meaning but destroy surface similarity</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1690" data-end="1750">In other words:<br data-start="1705" data-end="1708">
you are merging <strong data-start="1724" data-end="1736">meanings</strong>, not strings.</p>
<hr data-start="1752" data-end="1755">
