<hr data-start="238" data-end="241">
<h2 data-start="243" data-end="304">Option A — Formalizing <code data-start="269" data-end="275">meld</code> as a Core Spherepop Operator</h2>
<p data-start="306" data-end="414"><strong data-start="306" data-end="315">Goal:</strong> Extend the calculus minimally to account for semantic merging as a first-class irreversible event.</p>
<h3 data-start="416" data-end="434">A1. Motivation</h3>
<ul data-start="435" data-end="583">
<li data-start="435" data-end="535">
<p data-start="437" data-end="535">Why pop, bind, refuse, and collapse are insufficient to describe convergence of parallel histories</p>
</li>
<li data-start="536" data-end="583">
<p data-start="538" data-end="583">Distinction between elimination and synthesis</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="585" data-end="613">A2. Definition of <code data-start="607" data-end="613">meld</code></h3>
<ul data-start="614" data-end="764">
<li data-start="614" data-end="667">
<p data-start="616" data-end="667">Input: two (or more) histories with shared ancestry</p>
</li>
<li data-start="668" data-end="724">
<p data-start="670" data-end="724">Output: a single new history with authoritative future</p>
</li>
<li data-start="725" data-end="764">
<p data-start="727" data-end="764">Irreversibility and non-commutativity</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="766" data-end="792">A3. Geometry of <code data-start="786" data-end="792">meld</code></h3>
<ul data-start="793" data-end="937">
<li data-start="793" data-end="843">
<p data-start="795" data-end="843"><code data-start="795" data-end="801">meld</code> as constrained quotient rather than union</p>
</li>
<li data-start="844" data-end="880">
<p data-start="846" data-end="880">Preservation of causal commitments</p>
</li>
<li data-start="881" data-end="937">
<p data-start="883" data-end="937">Loss of alternative phrasings as intentional exclusion</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="939" data-end="967">A4. Accounting Semantics</h3>
<ul data-start="968" data-end="1098">
<li data-start="968" data-end="1010">
<p data-start="970" data-end="1010">Cost of synthesis vs cost of elimination</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1011" data-end="1098">
<p data-start="1013" data-end="1098">Why <code data-start="1017" data-end="1023">meld</code> increases commitment without shrinking option-space in the same way as pop</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1100" data-end="1133">A5. Interaction with Collapse</h3>
<ul data-start="1134" data-end="1250">
<li data-start="1134" data-end="1180">
<p data-start="1136" data-end="1180"><code data-start="1136" data-end="1142">meld</code> as collapse under a preference policy</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1181" data-end="1212">
<p data-start="1183" data-end="1212">When <code data-start="1188" data-end="1194">meld</code> should be delayed</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1213" data-end="1250">
<p data-start="1215" data-end="1250">Failure modes (premature synthesis)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1252" data-end="1276">A6. Minimal Examples</h3>
<ul data-start="1277" data-end="1361">
<li data-start="1277" data-end="1304">
<p data-start="1279" data-end="1304">Two drafts of a paragraph</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1305" data-end="1328">
<p data-start="1307" data-end="1328">Competing definitions</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1329" data-end="1361">
<p data-start="1331" data-end="1361">Conflicting section structures</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1363" data-end="1366">
<h2 data-start="1368" data-end="1412">Option B — Semantic Merge Policy Language</h2>
<p data-start="1414" data-end="1514"><strong data-start="1414" data-end="1423">Goal:</strong> Specify <em data-start="1432" data-end="1437">how</em> merges happen without hard-coding decisions, enabling inspectable synthesis.</p>
<h3 data-start="1516" data-end="1534">B1. Motivation</h3>
<ul data-start="1535" data-end="1617">
<li data-start="1535" data-end="1581">
<p data-start="1537" data-end="1581">Why line-based diff is the wrong abstraction</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1582" data-end="1617">
<p data-start="1584" data-end="1617">Semantic roles vs surface strings</p>
</li>
</ul>
