</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\label</span></span><span>{cor:meld</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>sheafification}
Let </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\mathscr</span></span><span>{T}</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span> be the presheaf of local semantic proposals (or local history fragments) over a cover </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\mathcal</span></span><span>{U}=</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\{</span></span><span>U</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>i</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\}</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span>, and let </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\{</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\delta</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>i</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\in</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\mathscr</span></span><span>{T}(U</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>i)</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\}</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span> be a family of local sections that fails to glue due to overlap obstructions. Fix a merge policy </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\pi</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span> that selects an identification relation </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\sim</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\pi</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span> on the obstruction data (equivalently, specifies which distinctions on overlaps are to be treated as inessential for the target semantic object). Then there exists a canonical quotient/sheafification step
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\[</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\mathscr</span></span><span>{T}</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\;</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\Longrightarrow</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\;</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\mathscr</span></span><span>{T}</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">^</span></span><span>{</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\pi</span></span><span>}
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\]</span></span><span>
such that the images of the local sections </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\{</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\delta</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">_</span></span><span>i</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\}</span></span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span> become compatible in </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\mathscr</span></span><span>{T}</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">^</span></span><span>{</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\pi</span></span><span>}</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">$</span></span><span> and therefore glue uniquely to a global section
