<p data-start="30" data-end="149"><strong data-start="30" data-end="81">No, you do not need a table of contents comment</strong>, and in most journal-style articles you <strong data-start="122" data-end="148">should not include one</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="151" data-end="211">Here’s the precise breakdown so you can decide deliberately.</p>
<hr data-start="213" data-end="216">
<h2 data-start="218" data-end="256">1. Is a Table of Contents required?</h2>
<h3 data-start="258" data-end="282">For journal articles</h3>
<ul data-start="283" data-end="392">
<li data-start="283" data-end="303">
<p data-start="285" data-end="303">❌ <strong data-start="287" data-end="303">Not required</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="304" data-end="325">
<p data-start="306" data-end="325">❌ Often discouraged</p>
</li>
<li data-start="326" data-end="392">
<p data-start="328" data-end="392">❌ Rarely included unless the article is very long or survey-like</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="394" data-end="415">Most journals expect:</p>
<ul data-start="416" data-end="464">
<li data-start="416" data-end="425">
<p data-start="418" data-end="425">Title</p>
</li>
<li data-start="426" data-end="438">
<p data-start="428" data-end="438">Abstract</p>
</li>
<li data-start="439" data-end="455">
<p data-start="441" data-end="455">Introduction</p>
</li>
<li data-start="456" data-end="464">
<p data-start="458" data-end="464">Body</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="466" data-end="503">with <strong data-start="471" data-end="502">no table of contents at all</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="505" data-end="508">
<h3 data-start="510" data-end="565">For preprints, monographs, or long technical essays</h3>
<ul data-start="566" data-end="668">
<li data-start="566" data-end="578">
<p data-start="568" data-end="578">✅ Optional</p>
</li>
<li data-start="579" data-end="625">
<p data-start="581" data-end="625">✅ Sometimes helpful if the structure is deep</p>
</li>
<li data-start="626" data-end="668">
<p data-start="628" data-end="668">⚠️ Usually placed <strong data-start="646" data-end="668">after the abstract</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="670" data-end="750">But even here, it is <strong data-start="691" data-end="710">not a “comment”</strong> — it is an explicit structural element.</p>
<hr data-start="752" data-end="755">
<h2 data-start="757" data-end="802">2. Where would it go <em data-start="781" data-end="785">if</em> you include one?</h2>
<p data-start="804" data-end="872">If you <em data-start="811" data-end="815">do</em> include a table of contents, the canonical placement is:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="874" data-end="1004"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\maketitle</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\begin</span></span><span>{abstract}
...
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\end</span></span><span>{abstract}

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\tableofcontents</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\clearpage</span></span><span>   </span><span><span class="hljs-comment">% optional</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\section</span></span><span>{Introduction}
...
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1006" data-end="1098">You do <strong data-start="1013" data-end="1020">not</strong> put a “comment” announcing it.<br data-start="1051" data-end="1054">
The table of contents <em data-start="1076" data-end="1080">is</em> the announcement.</p>
<hr data-start="1100" data-end="1103">
<h2 data-start="1105" data-end="1143">3. Should <em data-start="1118" data-end="1124">this</em> paper include one?</h2>
<p data-start="1145" data-end="1176">For <em data-start="1149" data-end="1155">this</em> document as written:</p>
<h3 data-start="1178" data-end="1246">My strong recommendation: <strong data-start="1208" data-end="1246">Do not include a table of contents</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1248" data-end="1256">Reasons:</p>
<ol data-start="1258" data-end="1688">
<li data-start="1258" data-end="1404">
<p data-start="1261" data-end="1294"><strong data-start="1261" data-end="1294">The paper has a narrative arc</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1298" data-end="1404">
<li data-start="1298" data-end="1353">
<p data-start="1300" data-end="1353">Axiom → Mechanics → Synthesis → Generation → Geometry</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1357" data-end="1404">
<p data-start="1359" data-end="1404">A TOC would prematurely expose the punchlines</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1406" data-end="1523">
<p data-start="1409" data-end="1442"><strong data-start="1409" data-end="1442">Section titles are conceptual</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1446" data-end="1523">
<li data-start="1446" data-end="1494">
<p data-start="1448" data-end="1494">Readers benefit from discovering them in order</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1498" data-end="1523">
<p data-start="1500" data-end="1523">Not from skimming ahead</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1525" data-end="1642">
<p data-start="1528" data-end="1579"><strong data-start="1528" data-end="1579">This reads as a manifesto + formal paper hybrid</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1583" data-end="1642">
<li data-start="1583" data-end="1617">
<p data-start="1585" data-end="1617">TOCs are for reference documents</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1621" data-end="1642">
<p data-start="1623" data-end="1642">This is an argument</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1644" data-end="1688">
<p data-start="1647" data-end="1688"><strong data-start="1647" data-end="1688">Journals will likely remove it anyway</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="1690" data-end="1693">
<h2 data-start="1695" data-end="1732">4. When you <em data-start="1710" data-end="1718">should</em> add one later</h2>
<p data-start="1734" data-end="1760">You <em data-start="1738" data-end="1746">should</em> add a TOC if:</p>
<ul data-start="1762" data-end="1941">
<li data-start="1762" data-end="1858">
<p data-start="1764" data-end="1783">You spin this into:</p>
<ul data-start="1786" data-end="1858">
<li data-start="1786" data-end="1800">
<p data-start="1788" data-end="1800">a monograph,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1803" data-end="1824">
<p data-start="1805" data-end="1824">a technical report,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1827" data-end="1858">
<p data-start="1829" data-end="1858">or Spherepop OS documentation</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1859" data-end="1909">
<p data-start="1861" data-end="1909">You add appendices that readers may jump between</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1910" data-end="1941">
<p data-start="1912" data-end="1941">You expect non-linear reading</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1943" data-end="2073">In that case, it belongs <strong data-start="1968" data-end="1990">after the abstract</strong> and before the introduction, exactly as you asked — but it’s a different document.</p>
<hr data-start="2075" data-end="2078">
<h2 data-start="2080" data-end="2116">5. Minimal toggle (best practice)</h2>
<p data-start="2118" data-end="2226">If you want to keep the option open without committing, you can leave this in your source <strong data-start="2208" data-end="2225">commented out</strong>:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2228" data-end="2272"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-comment">% \tableofcontents</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">% \clearpage</span></span><span>
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="2274" data-end="2283">That way:</p>
<ul data-start="2284" data-end="2347">
<li data-start="2284" data-end="2309">
<p data-start="2286" data-end="2309">the structure is ready,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2310" data-end="2347">
<p data-start="2312" data-end="2347">but the compiled paper stays clean.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2349" data-end="2352">
<h3 data-start="2354" data-end="2369">Bottom line</h3>
<ul data-start="2371" data-end="2532">
<li data-start="2371" data-end="2390">
<p data-start="2373" data-end="2390"><strong data-start="2373" data-end="2390">No TOC needed</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2391" data-end="2421">
<p data-start="2393" data-end="2421"><strong data-start="2393" data-end="2421">No comment announcing it</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2422" data-end="2470">
<p data-start="2424" data-end="2470"><strong data-start="2424" data-end="2470">Abstract → Introduction → Axiom is correct</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2471" data-end="2532">
<p data-start="2473" data-end="2532">Your current structure is exactly right for a serious paper</p>
