In that case, here is the <strong data-start="62" data-end="89">precise, correct answer</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="92" data-end="95">
<h2 data-start="97" data-end="152">Do you need a LaTeX command for a table of contents?</h2>
<p data-start="154" data-end="231"><strong data-start="154" data-end="231">No. You only need one if you actually want a table of contents to appear.</strong></p>
<p data-start="233" data-end="365">There is <strong data-start="242" data-end="265">no required command</strong> that must be placed after the abstract and before the introduction unless you intend to show a TOC.</p>
<hr data-start="367" data-end="370">
<h2 data-start="372" data-end="403">The only relevant command is</h2>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="405" data-end="434"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\tableofcontents</span></span><span>
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="436" data-end="497">That’s it. There is no other “comment” or “command” involved.</p>
<hr data-start="499" data-end="502">
<h2 data-start="504" data-end="536">Where it goes (if you use it)</h2>
<p data-start="538" data-end="609">If you decide to include a table of contents, the correct placement is:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="611" data-end="752"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\maketitle</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\begin</span></span><span>{abstract}
...
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\end</span></span><span>{abstract}

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\tableofcontents</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\clearpage</span></span><span>   </span><span><span class="hljs-comment">% optional but common</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\section</span></span><span>{Introduction}
...
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<ul data-start="754" data-end="814">
<li data-start="754" data-end="780">
<p data-start="756" data-end="780"><code data-start="756" data-end="768">\clearpage</code> is optional</p>
</li>
<li data-start="781" data-end="814">
<p data-start="783" data-end="814">Journals often remove it anyway</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="816" data-end="819">
<h2 data-start="821" data-end="874">For your document, the recommendation still stands</h2>
<p data-start="876" data-end="895">For <strong data-start="880" data-end="894">this paper</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="897" data-end="1031">
<li data-start="897" data-end="939">
<p data-start="899" data-end="939">❌ You do <strong data-start="908" data-end="915">not</strong> need <code data-start="921" data-end="939">\tableofcontents</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="940" data-end="987">
<p data-start="942" data-end="987">❌ You do <strong data-start="951" data-end="958">not</strong> need any placeholder command</p>
</li>
<li data-start="988" data-end="1031">
<p data-start="990" data-end="1031">❌ You do <strong data-start="999" data-end="1006">not</strong> need a comment or marker</p>
</li>
